



# Icons
- Use Lucide React for icons throughout the application.
- Keep icon usage consistent with the existing design system.


# Data Fetching & Forms
- Use TanStack Query (react-query) for frontend data fetching.
- Use React Hook Form for form handling.
- Use Zod for validation.
- Validation schemas are stored in `@qco/validators`.

# State Management & Logic
- Use React Context for state management.

# Backend & Database
Use Drizzle for database access.

# Database Schema
- Database schemas are defined in `@qco/db`.
- Use Drizzle ORM for database operations.
- Follow the schema definitions when creating new database models.


# tRPC & TanStack Query
- Use tRPC for type-safe API communication between backend and frontend.
- Follow examples in docs/trpc-tanstack-examples.md for implementing queries and mutations.
- Use the useTRPC hook for accessing tRPC procedures.
- Properly handle loading states, errors, and success cases.
- Use queryClient.invalidateQueries for cache invalidation after mutations.
- Leverage type inference capabilities provided by tRPC.

